Superheterodyne reciever is what we need to add to our reciever for it to be able to switch between stations. 

https://www.nutsvolts.com/magazine/article/a_simple_superhet


https://www.snapeda.com/parts/ST-1710007/Adlink/view-part/
^^^ speaker we will use for final product
reason for this is speaker and op amp need to match power outputs
https://www.ti.com/lit/ds/symlink/lm386.pdf
^^^ data sheet for our op amp
we are using the lm386 because it has low distortion while also operating with low voltage.
For our purposes we are using battery power for our radio, pulling high voltage from those batteries would cause us to have to account for it with other design considerations
Using a lower voltage for this point allows us more breathing room
https://www.quora.com/How-do-I-make-an-audio-amplifier-which-works-on-low-voltage-but-gives-the-maximum-amount-of-sound
^^^ good general information

